description: Application for a Non-Material Amendment (S96a) to vary condition 26 (approved drawings) of planning permission ref. 164694FUL dated 01/09/2017 for "Phased redevelopment comprising a residential-led mixed use masterplan incorporating 1,965 residential units; 21,443 sqm. of flexible commercial and community floor space in use classes A1/A2/A3/A4/A5/B1/D1 and/or D2 including a two form entry primary school and nursery; a pedestrian / cycle bridge across the Grand Union Canal; car and cycle parking; site wide landscaping and associated works, including highway works; following the demolition of buildings and structures on the site (with the exception of the original elements of the Grade II listed Glaxo House). Buildings / blocks will range in height between two-storeys and 19-storeys.  Amendment seeks development of block 5 using modular construction, additional windows to improve internal lighting; column positions, windows materials and internal space and ceiling height configurations
